response.headline: Tokyo travel recommendations featuring Mabashi Inari Shrine, Tonogayato Garden, and Edo-Tokyo Open Air Museum
response.summary: Mabashi Inari Shrine stands out as one of Tokyo's weirdest shrines with an entrance built into a residential building. Tonogayato Garden offers wide open spaces with seasonal flowers for just 150 Yen entrance fee. Edo-Tokyo Open Air Architectural Museum features unique architectural buildings from across Japan.
